{"at":804609646.407885,"id":"54-117","ticketId":"54","outcome":{"note":{}},"detail":"Here is my complete investigation report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Stack & Structure\n\nThis is a **monorepo** (`vokda`) — root directories:\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `apps\/web\/` | **SvelteKit** frontend (where the work lives) |\n| `apps\/api\/` | Backend API |\n| `packages\/sdk\/` | `@vokda\/sdk` TypeScript SDK for the TTS API |\n| `packages\/shared\/` | Placeholder (README only) |\n| `sdks\/` | Go, Python, Rust SDKs |\n\nThe target is the **SvelteKit web app** at `apps\/web\/`:\n- **Framework**: Svelte 4 + SvelteKit 2\n- **Language**: TypeScript 5.4, strict mode, ES modules\n- **Test runner**: Vitest 4 (config: `vitest.config.ts`), jsdom environment, globals enabled\n- **Test file pattern**: `src\/**\/*.test.ts`\n- **Test command**: `vitest run` (from `apps\/web\/`)\n\n---\n\n## 2. The text-utilities Module (delivered in #48)\n\nLocated at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/`:\n\n```\ntext-utilities\/\n├── index.ts              ← barrel re-export\n├── normalize-text.ts     ← normalizeText (pure, collapses whitespace)\n├── word-count.ts         ← wordCount (wraps normalizeText → split(' ') → length)\n├── truncate-words.ts     ← truncateWords (wraps normalizeText → split → slice + ellipsis)\n└── index.test.ts         ← all tests (vitest describe\/it\/expect)\n```\n\n### `index.ts` — current exports\n```ts\nexport { normalizeText } from '.\/normalize-text';\nexport { wordCount } from '.\/word-count';\nexport { truncateWords } from '.\/truncate-words';\n```\n\n### `wordCount` signature & behavior\n```ts\nexport function wordCount(text: string): number\n```\n- Normalizes via `normalizeText` (collapses all whitespace runs to single spaces, trims).\n- Returns `0` if normalized result is `\"\"`.\n- Otherwise returns `normalised.split(' ').length`.\n- Pure function, no side effects.\n- Tokenization is **space-delimited**, not locale-aware — as called out in the issue's out-of-scope.\n\n### `normalizeText` signature & behavior\n```ts\nexport function normalizeText(text: string): string\n```\n- `text.replace(\/\\s+\/g, ' ').trim()`\n- Pure. Returns `\"\"` for empty or whitespace-only input.\n\n### Test patterns (from `index.test.ts`)\n- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`\n- Module under test imported from the barrel: `import { normalizeText, wordCount, truncateWords } from '.\/index'`\n- Organization: one top-level `describe` per function, each with focused `it` blocks.\n- Existing `wordCount` tests cover: empty string → 0, whitespace-only → 0, single word → 1, two words → 2, extra internal spaces, newlines, leading\/trailing whitespace, mixed whitespace.\n\n---\n\n## 3. What This Work Item (#54) Requires\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| **New function** | `estimateReadingTime(text: string, wordsPerMinute?: number): number` |\n| **Where** | New file `estimate-reading-time.ts` in the same directory |\n| **Barrel export** | Add to `index.ts` |\n| **Implementation** | Must call the existing `wordCount(text)` — reuse, do not re-tokenize |\n| **Return value** | Whole minutes rounded up via `Math.ceil`; minimum `0` for empty\/whitespace-only |\n| **Default wpm** | `200` when `wordsPerMinute` is omitted |\n| **Tests** | Add a `describe('estimateReadingTime', ...)` block to `index.test.ts` |\n| **Test cases** | 1) empty string → 0; 2) 200 words @ 200wpm → 1; 3) 201 words @ 200wpm → 2; 4) custom wpm (e.g. 100 words @ 100wpm → 1) |\n| **Do NOT change** | `wordCount`, `normalizeText`, `truncateWords`, or their existing tests |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Key Facts for the Implementation Agent\n\n- **`wordCount` is imported from `'.\/word-count'`** (relative import within the module). The new function will likewise `import { wordCount } from '.\/word-count'`.\n- **The barrel file** at `index.ts` uses named re-exports — the new function should follow the same pattern.\n- **Tests** live in a single `index.test.ts` file; the new tests should be appended as a new `describe` block, matching the existing style (vitest, imports from `'.\/index'`).\n- **No changes** to `word-count.ts`, `normalize-text.ts`, `truncate-words.ts`, or their existing test cases.\n- **Test run command**: `cd apps\/web && npx vitest run` (or `npm test`).\n\n---\n\nThat covers every fact needed to produce the implementation. The work is scoped, bounded, and the existing code patterns are clear.","phase":"decompose"}
